tly the=C2=A0opposite=C2=A0reason: Inflation was persistently high, interes=
t rates went up, and those banks had to pay more on deposits even as their =
holdings of Treasury bonds lost value. Silicon Valley Bank was not subject =
to the Fed=E2=80=99s stress tests, as a mid-sized bank, but if it had been =
it would have done great! It did not do great in real life.
Anyway yesterday the 23 big banks subject to the stress tests   all passed.=
=C2=A0Here are the Fed=E2=80=99s  press release and=C2=A0the full=C2=A0resu=
lts. One of the banks that passed is the US arm of Credit Suisse Group=C2=
=A0AG, which survived the Fed=E2=80=99s hypothetical stress scenario just f=
