s test and (2) is closer to what actually happened:

In February 2023, for the first time, the Federal Reserve published an addi=
tional, exploratory market shock component that applied only to U.S. G-SIBs=
.=C2=A0The purpose of the stress test is to understand a firm=E2=80=99s=C2=
=A0 resilience to a range of severe but plausible events, and the explorato=
ry component furthers that purpose by posing a different set of risks than =
is probed by this year=E2=80=99s global market shock component.
In contrast to this year=E2=80=99s global market shock component, which was=
 characterized by a severe recession=C2=A0 with fading inflation expectatio=
ns, the exploratory market shock is characterized by a less severe recessio=
n with greater inflationary pressures induced by higher inflation expectati=
ons, increases in interest rates, an appreciation of the U.S. dollar, and i=
