<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In February 2023, for the first time, the Fede=
ral Reserve published an additional, exploratory market shock component tha=
t applied only to U.S. G-SIBs.=C2=A0The purpose of the stress test is to un=
derstand a firm=E2=80=99s=C2=A0 resilience to a range of severe but plausib=
le events, and the exploratory component furthers that purpose by posing a =
different set of risks than is probed by this year=E2=80=99s global market =
shock component.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In contrast to this year=E2=80=99s global mark=
et shock component, which was characterized by a severe recession=C2=A0 wit=
h fading inflation expectations, the exploratory market shock is characteri=
zed by a less severe recession with greater inflationary pressures induced =
by higher inflation expectations, increases in interest rates, an appreciat=
ion of the U.S. dollar, and increases in commodity prices.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This scenario doesn=E2=80=99t count for bank c=
apital requirements =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9CConsistent with the nature of a=
n exploratory exercise, the exploratory market shock will not contribute to=
